\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The screens sizes that Bootstrap uses are not random, but rather based on
 research on common device sizes.
 While you can change the screen sizes, because Bootstrap does use CSS,
 you want to use the defaults provided.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Lab
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Part 1 Notes, Steps and Scenario
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Lab Notes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Labs are designed to both be a challenge as well as real-world.
 As a result, full step-by-step instructions are not provided.
 However, all of the needed information, class names, and resources to complete
 the labs have been provided.
 This content is either in the videos provded, or in the resources section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you do get stuck you are free to discuss the lab with other students.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Keep in mind that future labs will continue to build on this one.
 Successful completion of the labs will require completing the labs from
 the module prior.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Lab Steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each lab will provide various resources.
 As you attempt the lab, try to solve the lab by using the earliest step
 possible.
 Here are the resources provided for this lab:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Wireframe.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the real world, a wireframe is generated to represent the design the
 business owner desires.
 Being able to translate a wireframe into a final product is a key skill
 all web developers need to have.
 Remember, a wireframe does not need to be matched exactly; a wireframe
 is intended to be a rough sketch of the desired result.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate-Resume
Screenshot 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you're just getting started, or if the wireframe isn't clear about the
 target design, you can look at the screenshot.
 This is a sample of what the final result should look like.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate-Resume
Additional guidance 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The additional guidance is provided to add clarity and help add context
 if needed.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Lab Scenario
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You have been tasked with creating a page to display the details of a record
 album.
 You will build this page up over the course of the next several labs.
 The starting page only needs to target medium and large devices; support
 for smaller devices will be added later.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These are the necessary components:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
A banner to display the name of the music store, Music Store 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Album information 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
An image on the left side to represent the cover art.
 The image is provided here.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The basic information on the album on the right side.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally, you have been requested to implement a new theme that is different
 from the default.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You are free to choose whatever theme you like, and are free to determine
 the sizing that you believe will work best for the page.
\end_layout

