\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Part 4 Additional Guidance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Download Bootstrap components from www.getbootstrap.com.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Download the album art.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Create a new project in Visual Studio.
 Use the empty web template.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Add a folder named "Styles".
 Add the Bootstrap css files to this folder.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Add a folder named "Scripts".
 Add the JavaScript files to this folder.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Add a new HTML page named AlbumDetails.html.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Add references to the Bootstrap min CSS file to AlbumDetails.html.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Add the necessary HTML to implement the layout.
 Use the phrases Music Store, Album Title, and Artist as placeholders as
 shown in the wireframe.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Obtain a new theme from bootswatch.com.
 Implement the new theme.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Page Design and Data Display
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bootstrap offers several features to ensure your page is designed optimally
 for all screen sizes.
 You'll examine how to best use those capabilities to ensure users can easily
 consume the data they need regardless of their device type.
 You'll also see how to use some of the advanced components, or controls,
 that Bootstrap offers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Forms and User Interaction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We'll close our exploration of Bootstrap by taking a look at how we can
 obtain data from the user and provide feedback.
 Bootstrap offers great support for customizing forms, and several options
 to let the user know when the form is correct or incorrect.
 You'll see how to add alerts and modal dialog boxes, as well as inline
 validation and data prompts.
\end_layout

